text: Dex Number: #0001 Bulbasaur Grass · Poison Name: Bulbasaur Type: Grass, Poison Description: A strange seed was planted on its back at birth. The plant sprouts and grows with this POKéMON.
Dex Number: #0002 Ivysaur Grass · Poison Name: Ivysaur Type: Grass, Poison Description: When the bulb on its back grows large, it appears to lose the ability to stand on its hind legs.
Dex Number: #0003 Venusaur Grass · Poison Name: Venusaur Type: Grass, Poison Description: The plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.
Dex Number: #0004 Charmander Fire Name: Charmander Type: Fire Description: Obviously prefers hot places. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.
Dex Number: #0005 Charmeleon Fire Name: Charmeleon Type: Fire Description: When it swings its burning tail, it elevates the temperature to unbearably high levels.
Dex Number: #0006 Charizard Fire · Flying Name: Charizard Type: Fire, Flying Description: Spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. Known to cause forest fires unintentionally.
Dex Number: #0007 Squirtle Water Name: Squirtle Type: Water Description: After birth, its back swells and hardens into a shell. Powerfully sprays foam from its mouth.
Dex Number: #0008 Wartortle Water Name: Wartortle Type: Water Description: Often hides in water to stalk unwary prey. For swimming fast, it moves its ears to maintain balance.
Dex Number: #0009 Blastoise Water Name: Blastoise Type: Water Description: A brutal POKéMON with pressurized water jets on its shell. They are used for high speed tackles.
Dex Number: #0010 Caterpie Bug Name: Caterpie Type: Bug Description: Its short feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to tirelessly climb slopes and walls.
Dex Number: #0011 Metapod Bug Name: Metapod Type: Bug Description: This POKéMON is vulnerable to attack while its shell is soft, exposing its weak and tender body.
Dex Number: #0012 Butterfree Bug · Flying Name: Butterfree Type: Bug, Flying Description: In battle, it flaps its wings at high speed to release highly toxic dust into the air.
Dex Number: #0013 Weedle Bug · Poison Name: Weedle Type: Bug, Poison Description: Often found in forests, eating leaves. It has a sharp venomous stinger on its head.
Dex Number: #0014 Kakuna Bug · Poison Name: Kakuna Type: Bug, Poison Description: Almost incapable of moving, this POKéMON can only harden its shell to protect itself from predators.
Dex Number: #0015 Beedrill Bug · Poison Name: Beedrill Type: Bug, Poison Description: Flies at high speed and attacks using its large venomous stingers on its forelegs and tail.
Dex Number: #0016 Pidgey Normal · Flying Name: Pidgey Type: Normal, Flying Description: A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.
Dex Number: #0017 Pidgeotto Normal · Flying Name: Pidgeotto Type: Normal, Flying Description: Very protective of its sprawling territorial area, this POKéMON will fiercely peck at any intruder.
Dex Number: #0018 Pidgeot Normal · Flying Name: Pidgeot Type: Normal, Flying Description: When hunting, it skims the surface of water at high speed to pick off unwary prey such as MAGIKARP.
Dex Number: #0019 Rattata Normal Name: Rattata Type: Normal Description: Bites anything when it attacks. Small and very quick, it is a common sight in many places.
Dex Number: #0020 Raticate Normal Name: Raticate Type: Normal Description: It uses its whiskers to maintain its balance. It apparently slows down if they are cut off.
Dex Number: #0021 Spearow Normal · Flying Name: Spearow Type: Normal, Flying Description: Eats bugs in grassy areas. It has to flap its short wings at high speed to stay airborne.
Dex Number: #0022 Fearow Normal · Flying Name: Fearow Type: Normal, Flying Description: With its huge and magnificent wings, it can keep aloft without ever having to land for rest.
Dex Number: #0023 Ekans Poison Name: Ekans Type: Poison Description: Moves silently and stealthily. Eats the eggs of birds, such as PIDGEY and SPEAROW, whole.
Dex Number: #0024 Arbok Poison Name: Arbok Type: Poison Description: It is rumored that the ferocious warning markings on its belly differ from area to area.
Dex Number: #0025 Pikachu Electric Name: Pikachu Type: Electric Description: When several of these POKéMON gather, their electricity could build and cause lightning storms.
Dex Number: #0026 Raichu Electric Name: Raichu Type: Electric Description: Its long tail serves as a ground to protect itself from its own high voltage power.
Dex Number: #0027 Sandshrew Ground Name: Sandshrew Type: Ground Description: Burrows deep underground in arid locations far from water. It only emerges to hunt for food.
Dex Number: #0028 Sandslash Ground Name: Sandslash Type: Ground Description: Curls up into a spiny ball when threatened. It can roll while curled up to attack or escape.
Dex Number: #0029 Nidoran♀ Poison Name: Nidoran♀ Type: Poison Description: Although small, its venomous barbs render this POKéMON dangerous. The female has smaller horns.
Dex Number: #0030 Nidorina Poison Name: Nidorina Type: Poison Description: The female’s horn develops slowly. Prefers physical attacks such as clawing and biting.
Dex Number: #0031 Nidoqueen Poison · Ground Name: Nidoqueen Type: Poison, Ground Description: Its hard scales provide strong protection. It uses its hefty bulk to execute powerful moves.
Dex Number: #0032 Nidoran♂ Poison Name: Nidoran♂ Type: Poison Description: Stiffens its ears to sense danger. The larger its horns, the more powerful its secreted venom.
Dex Number: #0033 Nidorino Poison Name: Nidorino Type: Poison Description: An aggressive POKéMON that is quick to attack. The horn on its head secretes a powerful venom.
Dex Number: #0034 Nidoking Poison · Ground Name: Nidoking Type: Poison, Ground Description: It uses its powerful tail in battle to smash, constrict, then break the prey’s bones.
Dex Number: #0035 Clefairy Fairy Name: Clefairy Type: Fairy Description: Its magical and cute appeal has many admirers. It is rare and found only in certain areas.
Dex Number: #0036 Clefable Fairy Name: Clefable Type: Fairy Description: A timid fairy POKéMON that is rarely seen. It will run and hide the moment it senses people.
Dex Number: #0037 Vulpix Fire Name: Vulpix Type: Fire Description: At the time of birth, it has just one tail. The tail splits from its tip as it grows older.
Dex Number: #0038 Ninetales Fire Name: Ninetales Type: Fire Description: Very smart and very vengeful. Grabbing one of its many tails could result in a 1000-year curse.
Dex Number: #0039 Jigglypuff Normal · Fairy Name: Jigglypuff Type: Normal, Fairy Description: When its huge eyes light up, it sings a mysteriously soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.
Dex Number: #0040 Wigglytuff Normal · Fairy Name: Wigglytuff Type: Normal, Fairy Description: The body is soft and rubbery. When angered, it will suck in air and inflate itself to an enormous size.
Dex Number: #0041 Zubat Poison · Flying Name: Zubat Type: Poison, Flying Description: Forms colonies in perpetually dark places. Uses ultrasonic waves to identify and approach targets.
Dex Number: #0042 Golbat Poison · Flying Name: Golbat Type: Poison, Flying Description: Once it strikes, it will not stop draining energy from the victim even if it gets too heavy to fly.
Dex Number: #0043 Oddish Grass · Poison Name: Oddish Type: Grass, Poison Description: During the day, it keeps its face buried in the ground. At night, it wanders around sowing its seeds.
Dex Number: #0044 Gloom Grass · Poison Name: Gloom Type: Grass, Poison Description: The fluid that oozes from its mouth isn’t drool. It is a nectar that is used to attract prey.
Dex Number: #0045 Vileplume Grass · Poison Name: Vileplume Type: Grass, Poison Description: The larger its petals, the more toxic pollen it contains. Its big head is heavy and hard to hold up.
Dex Number: #0046 Paras Bug · Grass Name: Paras Type: Bug, Grass Description: Burrows to suck tree roots. The mushrooms on its back grow by drawing nutrients from the bug host.
Dex Number: #0047 Parasect Bug · Grass Name: Parasect Type: Bug, Grass Description: A host-parasite pair in which the parasite mushroom has taken over the host bug. Prefers damp places.
Dex Number: #0048 Venonat Bug · Poison Name: Venonat Type: Bug, Poison Description: Lives in the shadows of tall trees where it eats insects. It is attracted by light at night.
Dex Number: #0049 Venomoth Bug · Poison Name: Venomoth Type: Bug, Poison Description: The dust-like scales covering its wings are color coded to indicate the kinds of poison it has.
Dex Number: #0050 Diglett Ground Name: Diglett Type: Ground Description: Lives about one yard underground where it feeds on plant roots. It sometimes appears above ground.
Dex Number: #0051 Dugtrio Ground Name: Dugtrio Type: Ground Description: A team of DIGLETT triplets. It triggers huge earthquakes by burrowing 60 miles underground.
Dex Number: #0052 Meowth Normal Name: Meowth Type: Normal Description: Adores circular objects. Wanders the streets on a nightly basis to look for dropped loose change.
Dex Number: #0053 Persian Normal Name: Persian Type: Normal Description: Although its fur has many admirers, it is tough to raise as a pet because of its fickle meanness.
Dex Number: #0054 Psyduck Water Name: Psyduck Type: Water Description: While lulling its enemies with its vacant look, this wily POKéMON will use psychokinetic powers.
Dex Number: #0055 Golduck Water Name: Golduck Type: Water Description: Often seen swimming elegantly by lake shores. It is often mistaken for the Japanese monster, Kappa.
Dex Number: #0056 Mankey Fighting Name: Mankey Type: Fighting Description: Extremely quick to anger. It could be docile one moment then thrashing away the next instant.
Dex Number: #0057 Primeape Fighting Name: Primeape Type: Fighting Description: Always furious and tenacious to boot. It will not abandon chasing its quarry until it is caught.
Dex Number: #0058 Growlithe Fire Name: Growlithe Type: Fire Description: Very protective of its territory. It will bark and bite to repel intruders from its space.
Dex Number: #0059 Arcanine Fire Name: Arcanine Type: Fire Description: A POKéMON that has been admired since the past for its beauty. It runs agilely as if on wings.
Dex Number: #0060 Poliwag Water Name: Poliwag Type: Water Description: Its newly grown legs prevent it from running. It appears to prefer swimming than trying to stand.
Dex Number: #0061 Poliwhirl Water Name: Poliwhirl Type: Water Description: Capable of living in or out of water. When out of water, it sweats to keep its body slimy.
Dex Number: #0062 Poliwrath Water · Fighting Name: Poliwrath Type: Water, Fighting Description: An adept swimmer at both the front crawl and breast stroke. Easily overtakes the best human swimmers.
Dex Number: #0063 Abra Psychic Name: Abra Type: Psychic Description: Using its ability to read minds, it will identify impending danger and TELEPORT to safety.
Dex Number: #0064 Kadabra Psychic Name: Kadabra Type: Psychic Description: It emits special alpha waves from its body that induce headaches just by being close by.
Dex Number: #0065 Alakazam Psychic Name: Alakazam Type: Psychic Description: Its brain can outperform a supercomputer. Its intelligence quotient is said to be 5,000.
Dex Number: #0066 Machop Fighting Name: Machop Type: Fighting Description: Loves to build its muscles. It trains in all styles of martial arts to become even stronger.
Dex Number: #0067 Machoke Fighting Name: Machoke Type: Fighting Description: Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a power save belt to be able to regulate its motions.
Dex Number: #0068 Machamp Fighting Name: Machamp Type: Fighting Description: Using its heavy muscles, it throws powerful punches that can send the victim clear over the horizon.
Dex Number: #0069 Bellsprout Grass · Poison Name: Bellsprout Type: Grass, Poison Description: A carnivorous POKéMON that traps and eats bugs. It uses its root feet to soak up needed moisture.
Dex Number: #0070 Weepinbell Grass · Poison Name: Weepinbell Type: Grass, Poison Description: It spits out POISONPOWDER to immobilize the enemy and then finishes it with a spray of ACID.
Dex Number: #0071 Victreebel Grass · Poison Name: Victreebel Type: Grass, Poison Description: Said to live in huge colonies deep in jungles, although no one has ever returned from there.
Dex Number: #0072 Tentacool Water · Poison Name: Tentacool Type: Water, Poison Description: Drifts in shallow seas. Anglers who hook them by accident are often punished by its stinging acid.
Dex Number: #0073 Tentacruel Water · Poison Name: Tentacruel Type: Water, Poison Description: The tentacles are normally kept short. On hunts, they are extended to ensnare and immobilize prey.
Dex Number: #0074 Geodude Rock · Ground Name: Geodude Type: Rock, Ground Description: Found in fields and mountains. Mistaking them for boulders, people often step or trip on them.
Dex Number: #0075 Graveler Rock · Ground Name: Graveler Type: Rock, Ground Description: Rolls down slopes to move. It rolls over any obstacle without slowing or changing its direction.
Dex Number: #0076 Golem Rock · Ground Name: Golem Type: Rock, Ground Description: Its boulder-like body is extremely hard. It can easily withstand dynamite blasts without damage.
Dex Number: #0077 Ponyta Fire Name: Ponyta Type: Fire Description: Its hooves are 10 times harder than diamonds. It can trample anything completely flat in little time.
Dex Number: #0078 Rapidash Fire Name: Rapidash Type: Fire Description: Very competitive, this POKéMON will chase anything that moves fast in the hopes of racing it.
Dex Number: #0079 Slowpoke Water · Psychic Name: Slowpoke Type: Water, Psychic Description: Incredibly slow and dopey. It takes 5 seconds for it to feel pain when under attack.
Dex Number: #0080 Slowbro Water · Psychic Name: Slowbro Type: Water, Psychic Description: The SHELLDER that is latched onto SLOWPOKE’s tail is said to feed on the host’s left over scraps.
Dex Number: #0081 Magnemite Electric · Steel Name: Magnemite Type: Electric, Steel Description: Uses anti-gravity to stay suspended. Appears without warning and uses THUNDER WAVE and similar moves.
Dex Number: #0082 Magneton Electric · Steel Name: Magneton Type: Electric, Steel Description: Formed by several MAGNEMITEs linked together. They frequently appear when sunspots flare up.
Dex Number: #0083 Farfetch'd Normal · Flying Name: Farfetch'd Type: Normal, Flying Description: The sprig of green onions it holds is its weapon. It is used much like a metal sword.
Dex Number: #0084 Doduo Normal · Flying Name: Doduo Type: Normal, Flying Description: A bird that makes up for its poor flying with its fast foot speed. Leaves giant footprints.
Dex Number: #0085 Dodrio Normal · Flying Name: Dodrio Type: Normal, Flying Description: Uses its three brains to execute complex plans. While two heads sleep, one head stays awake.
Dex Number: #0086 Seel Water Name: Seel Type: Water Description: The protruding horn on its head is very hard. It is used for bashing through thick ice.
Dex Number: #0087 Dewgong Water · Ice Name: Dewgong Type: Water, Ice Description: Stores thermal energy in its body. Swims at a steady 8 knots even in intensely cold waters.
Dex Number: #0088 Grimer Poison Name: Grimer Type: Poison Description: Appears in filthy areas. Thrives by sucking up polluted sludge that is pumped out of factories.
Dex Number: #0089 Muk Poison Name: Muk Type: Poison Description: Thickly covered with a filthy, vile sludge. It is so toxic, even its footprints contain poison.
Dex Number: #0090 Shellder Water Name: Shellder Type: Water Description: Its hard shell repels any kind of attack. It is vulnerable only when its shell is open.
Dex Number: #0091 Cloyster Water · Ice Name: Cloyster Type: Water, Ice Description: When attacked, it launches its horns in quick volleys. Its innards have never been seen.
Dex Number: #0092 Gastly Ghost · Poison Name: Gastly Type: Ghost, Poison Description: Almost invisible, this gaseous POKéMON cloaks the target and puts it to sleep without notice.
Dex Number: #0093 Haunter Ghost · Poison Name: Haunter Type: Ghost, Poison Description: Because of its ability to slip through block walls, it is said to be from another dimension.
Dex Number: #0094 Gengar Ghost · Poison Name: Gengar Type: Ghost, Poison Description: Under a full moon, this POKéMON likes to mimic the shadows of people and laugh at their fright.
Dex Number: #0095 Onix Rock · Ground Name: Onix Type: Rock, Ground Description: As it grows, the stone portions of its body harden to become similar to a diamond, but colored black.
Dex Number: #0096 Drowzee Psychic Name: Drowzee Type: Psychic Description: Puts enemies to sleep then eats their dreams. Occasionally gets sick from eating bad dreams.
Dex Number: #0097 Hypno Psychic Name: Hypno Type: Psychic Description: When it locks eyes with an enemy, it will use a mix of PSI moves such as HYPNOSIS and CONFUSION.
Dex Number: #0098 Krabby Water Name: Krabby Type: Water Description: Its pincers are not only powerful weapons, they are used for balance when walking sideways.
Dex Number: #0099 Kingler Water Name: Kingler Type: Water Description: The large pincer has 10000 hp of crushing power. However, its huge size makes it unwieldy to use.
Dex Number: #0100 Voltorb Electric Name: Voltorb Type: Electric Description: Usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a POKé BALL, they have zapped many people.
Dex Number: #0101 Electrode Electric Name: Electrode Type: Electric Description: It stores electric energy under very high pressure. It often explodes with little or no provocation.
Dex Number: #0102 Exeggcute Grass · Psychic Name: Exeggcute Type: Grass, Psychic Description: Often mistaken for eggs. When disturbed, they quickly gather and attack in swarms.
Dex Number: #0103 Exeggutor Grass · Psychic Name: Exeggutor Type: Grass, Psychic Description: Legend has it that on rare occasions, one of its heads will drop off and continue on as an EXEGGCUTE.
Dex Number: #0104 Cubone Ground Name: Cubone Type: Ground Description: Because it never removes its skull helmet, no one has ever seen this POKéMON’s real face.
Dex Number: #0105 Marowak Ground Name: Marowak Type: Ground Description: The bone it holds is its key weapon. It throws the bone skillfully like a boomerang to KO targets.
Dex Number: #0106 Hitmonlee Fighting Name: Hitmonlee Type: Fighting Description: When in a hurry, its legs lengthen progressively. It runs smoothly with extra long, loping strides.
Dex Number: #0107 Hitmonchan Fighting Name: Hitmonchan Type: Fighting Description: While apparently doing nothing, it fires punches in lightning fast volleys that are impossible to see.
Dex Number: #0108 Lickitung Normal Name: Lickitung Type: Normal Description: Its tongue can be extended like a chameleon’s. It leaves a tingling sensation when it licks enemies.
Dex Number: #0109 Koffing Poison Name: Koffing Type: Poison Description: Because it stores several kinds of toxic gases in its body, it is prone to exploding without warning.
Dex Number: #0110 Weezing Poison Name: Weezing Type: Poison Description: Where two kinds of poison gases meet, 2 KOFFINGs can fuse into a WEEZING over many years.
Dex Number: #0111 Rhyhorn Ground · Rock Name: Rhyhorn Type: Ground, Rock Description: Its massive bones are 1000 times harder than human bones. It can easily knock a trailer flying.
Dex Number: #0112 Rhydon Ground · Rock Name: Rhydon Type: Ground, Rock Description: Protected by an armor-like hide, it is capable of living in molten lava of 3,600 degrees.
Dex Number: #0113 Chansey Normal Name: Chansey Type: Normal Description: A rare and elusive POKéMON that is said to bring happiness to those who manage to get it.
Dex Number: #0114 Tangela Grass Name: Tangela Type: Grass Description: The whole body is swathed with wide vines that are similar to seaweed. Its vines shake as it walks.
Dex Number: #0115 Kangaskhan Normal Name: Kangaskhan Type: Normal Description: The infant rarely ventures out of its mother’s protective pouch until it is 3 years old.
Dex Number: #0116 Horsea Water Name: Horsea Type: Water Description: Known to shoot down flying bugs with precision blasts of ink from the surface of the water.
Dex Number: #0117 Seadra Water Name: Seadra Type: Water Description: Capable of swimming backwards by rapidly flapping its wing-like pectoral fins and stout tail.
Dex Number: #0118 Goldeen Water Name: Goldeen Type: Water Description: Its tail fin billows like an elegant ballroom dress, giving it the nickname of the Water Queen.
Dex Number: #0119 Seaking Water Name: Seaking Type: Water Description: In the autumn spawning season, they can be seen swimming powerfully up rivers and creeks.
Dex Number: #0120 Staryu Water Name: Staryu Type: Water Description: An enigmatic POKéMON that can effortlessly regenerate any appendage it loses in battle.
Dex Number: #0121 Starmie Water · Psychic Name: Starmie Type: Water, Psychic Description: Its central core glows with the seven colors of the rainbow. Some people value the core as a gem.
Dex Number: #0122 Mr. Mime Psychic · Fairy Name: Mr. Mime Type: Psychic, Fairy Description: If interrupted while it is miming, it will slap around the offender with its broad hands.
Dex Number: #0123 Scyther Bug · Flying Name: Scyther Type: Bug, Flying Description: With ninja-like agility and speed, it can create the illusion that there is more than one.
Dex Number: #0124 Jynx Ice · Psychic Name: Jynx Type: Ice, Psychic Description: It seductively wiggles its hips as it walks. It can cause people to dance in unison with it.
Dex Number: #0125 Electabuzz Electric Name: Electabuzz Type: Electric Description: Normally found near power plants, they can wander away and cause major blackouts in cities.
Dex Number: #0126 Magmar Fire Name: Magmar Type: Fire Description: Its body always burns with an orange glow that enables it to hide perfectly among flames.
Dex Number: #0127 Pinsir Bug Name: Pinsir Type: Bug Description: If it fails to crush the victim in its pincers, it will swing it around and toss it hard.
Dex Number: #0128 Tauros Normal Name: Tauros Type: Normal Description: When it targets an enemy, it charges furiously while whipping its body with its long tails.
Dex Number: #0129 Magikarp Water Name: Magikarp Type: Water Description: In the distant past, it was somewhat stronger than the horribly weak descendants that exist today.
Dex Number: #0130 Gyarados Water · Flying Name: Gyarados Type: Water, Flying Description: Rarely seen in the wild. Huge and vicious, it is capable of destroying entire cities in a rage.
Dex Number: #0131 Lapras Water · Ice Name: Lapras Type: Water, Ice Description: A POKéMON that has been overhunted almost to extinction. It can ferry people across the water.
Dex Number: #0132 Ditto Normal Name: Ditto Type: Normal Description: Capable of copying an enemy’s genetic code to instantly transform itself into a duplicate of the enemy.
Dex Number: #0133 Eevee Normal Name: Eevee Type: Normal Description: Its genetic code is irregular. It may mutate if it is exposed to radiation from element STONEs.
Dex Number: #0134 Vaporeon Water Name: Vaporeon Type: Water Description: Lives close to water. Its long tail is ridged with a fin which is often mistaken for a mermaid’s.
Dex Number: #0135 Jolteon Electric Name: Jolteon Type: Electric Description: It accumulates negative ions in the atmosphere to blast out 10000-volt lightning bolts.
Dex Number: #0136 Flareon Fire Name: Flareon Type: Fire Description: When storing thermal energy in its body, its temperature could soar to over 1600 degrees.
Dex Number: #0137 Porygon Normal Name: Porygon Type: Normal Description: A POKéMON that consists entirely of programming code. Capable of moving freely in cyberspace.
Dex Number: #0138 Omanyte Rock · Water Name: Omanyte Type: Rock, Water Description: Although long extinct, in rare cases, it can be genetically resurrected from fossils.
Dex Number: #0139 Omastar Rock · Water Name: Omastar Type: Rock, Water Description: A prehistoric POKéMON that died out when its heavy shell made it impossible to catch prey.
Dex Number: #0140 Kabuto Rock · Water Name: Kabuto Type: Rock, Water Description: A POKéMON that was resurrected from a fossil found in what was once the ocean floor eons ago.
Dex Number: #0141 Kabutops Rock · Water Name: Kabutops Type: Rock, Water Description: Its sleek shape is perfect for swimming. It slashes prey with its claws and drains the body fluids.
Dex Number: #0142 Aerodactyl Rock · Flying Name: Aerodactyl Type: Rock, Flying Description: A ferocious, prehistoric POKéMON that goes for the enemy’s throat with its serrated saw-like fangs.
Dex Number: #0143 Snorlax Normal Name: Snorlax Type: Normal Description: Very lazy. Just eats and sleeps. As its rotund bulk builds, it becomes steadily more slothful.
Dex Number: #0144 Articuno Ice · Flying Name: Articuno Type: Ice, Flying Description: A legendary bird POKéMON that is said to appear to doomed people who are lost in icy mountains.
Dex Number: #0145 Zapdos Electric · Flying Name: Zapdos Type: Electric, Flying Description: A legendary bird POKéMON that is said to appear from clouds while dropping enormous lightning bolts.
Dex Number: #0146 Moltres Fire · Flying Name: Moltres Type: Fire, Flying Description: Known as the legendary bird of fire. Every flap of its wings creates a dazzling flash of flames.
Dex Number: #0147 Dratini Dragon Name: Dratini Type: Dragon Description: Long considered a mythical POKéMON until recently when a small colony was found living underwater.
Dex Number: #0148 Dragonair Dragon Name: Dragonair Type: Dragon Description: A mystical POKéMON that exudes a gentle aura. Has the ability to change climate conditions.
Dex Number: #0149 Dragonite Dragon · Flying Name: Dragonite Type: Dragon, Flying Description: An extremely rarely seen marine POKéMON. Its intelligence is said to match that of humans.
Dex Number: #0150 Mewtwo Psychic Name: Mewtwo Type: Psychic Description: It was created by a scientist after years of horrific gene splicing and DNA engineering experiments.
Dex Number: #0151 Mew Psychic Name: Mew Type: Psychic Description: So rare that it is still said to be a mirage by many experts. Only a few people have seen it worldwide.
Dex Number: #0152 Chikorita Grass Name: Chikorita Type: Grass Description: A sweet aroma gently wafts from the leaf on its head. It is docile and loves to soak up the sun’s rays.
Dex Number: #0153 Bayleef Grass Name: Bayleef Type: Grass Description: The scent of spices comes from around its neck. Somehow, sniffing it makes you want to fight.
Dex Number: #0154 Meganium Grass Name: Meganium Type: Grass Description: The aroma that rises from its petals contains a substance that calms aggressive feelings.
Dex Number: #0155 Cyndaquil Fire Name: Cyndaquil Type: Fire Description: It is timid, and always curls itself up in a ball. If attacked, it flares up its back for protection.
Dex Number: #0156 Quilava Fire Name: Quilava Type: Fire Description: Be careful if it turns its back during battle. It means that it will attack with the fire on its back.
Dex Number: #0157 Typhlosion Fire Name: Typhlosion Type: Fire Description: If its rage peaks, it becomes so hot that anything that touches it will instantly go up in flames.
Dex Number: #0158 Totodile Water Name: Totodile Type: Water Description: Its well-developed jaws are powerful and capable of crushing anything. Even its trainer must be careful.
Dex Number: #0159 Croconaw Water Name: Croconaw Type: Water Description: If it loses a fang, a new one grows back in its place. There are always 48 fangs lining its mouth.
Dex Number: #0160 Feraligatr Water Name: Feraligatr Type: Water Description: When it bites with its massive and powerful jaws, it shakes its head and savagely tears its victim up.
Dex Number: #0161 Sentret Normal Name: Sentret Type: Normal Description: A very cautious POKéMON, it raises itself up using its tail to get a better view of its surroundings.
Dex Number: #0162 Furret Normal Name: Furret Type: Normal Description: It makes a nest to suit its long and skinny body. The nest is impossible for other POKéMON to enter.
Dex Number: #0163 Hoothoot Normal · Flying Name: Hoothoot Type: Normal, Flying Description: It always stands on one foot. It changes feet so fast, the movement can rarely be seen.
Dex Number: #0164 Noctowl Normal · Flying Name: Noctowl Type: Normal, Flying Description: Its eyes are specially adapted. They concentrate even faint light and enable it to see in the dark.
Dex Number: #0165 Ledyba Bug · Flying Name: Ledyba Type: Bug, Flying Description: It is very timid. It will be afraid to move if it is alone. But it will be active if it is in a group.
Dex Number: #0166 Ledian Bug · Flying Name: Ledian Type: Bug, Flying Description: When the stars flicker in the night sky, it flutters about, scattering a glowing powder.
Dex Number: #0167 Spinarak Bug · Poison Name: Spinarak Type: Bug, Poison Description: It lies still in the same pose for days in its web, waiting for its unsuspecting prey to wander close.
Dex Number: #0168 Ariados Bug · Poison Name: Ariados Type: Bug, Poison Description: It spins string not only from its rear but also from its mouth. It is hard to tell which end is which.
Dex Number: #0169 Crobat Poison · Flying Name: Crobat Type: Poison, Flying Description: It flies so silently through the dark on its four wings that it may not be noticed even when nearby.
Dex Number: #0170 Chinchou Water · Electric Name: Chinchou Type: Water, Electric Description: It shoots positive and negative electricity between the tips of its two antennae and zaps its enemies.
Dex Number: #0171 Lanturn Water · Electric Name: Lanturn Type: Water, Electric Description: The light it emits is so bright that it can illuminate the sea’s surface from a depth of over three miles.
Dex Number: #0172 Pichu Electric Name: Pichu Type: Electric Description: It is not yet skilled at storing electricity. It may send out a jolt if amused or startled.
Dex Number: #0173 Cleffa Fairy Name: Cleffa Type: Fairy Description: Because of its unusual, star-like silhouette, people believe that it came here on a meteor.
